unlike other music magazine, rockin'on japan tried to report of music and band whose style and genre were not so spotlighted. under pre-internet media environment, the magazine played a role of the bridge which ties the major scene with the minor, indie and underground scene.

usually music magazine are made in a big size. it's mainly for showing photo in particular. in the face of a situation where such format were thought as a norm, rockin'on japan chose the way that shrink the size of the magazine. it turned into a very handy, compact-book size one.

as if to prove the expectation that the editor in chief had, the music magazine rockin'on japan was gave a credit from people & turned into a popular music media, a linguistic platform about music to a certain extent. it was during the mid 90's to the early 00's in japan.
